If we assume that the drying time for one pair of socks is 10 hours, then drying time for 7 pairs of socks would be:

7 pairs x 10 hours per pair = 70 hours (or approximately 2.9 days)

Therefore, Tom can expect to wait for around 2.9 days for the seven pairs of socks to dry under the same weather conditions as before.
